    {
      "type": "eq",
      "start": 8,
      "end": 30,
      "html": "<section class=\"slide eq\"><ul class=\"eq-lines\"><li id=\"implyzvcf1v\" class=\" eq-item eq-title \" > Understanding the Square </li><li id=\"implyzvcf1w\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ (a+b)^2 $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcf1x\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = (a+b)(a+b) $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcf1y\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > Now every term must multiply. </li><li id=\"implyzvcf1z\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = a(a+b) + b(a+b) $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcf20\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = a^2 + ab + ab + b^2 $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcf21\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > The two middle terms are identical. </li><li id=\"implyzvcf22\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = a^2 + 2ab + b^2 $$ </li></ul><div class=\"eq-side-panel\"><div id=\"implyzvcf1v-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The exponent applies to the whole bracket. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf1v-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The bracket multiplies itself. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf1w-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > This is not a^2 + b^2. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf1x-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" ><img src=\"box.webp\" /></div><div id=\"implyzvcf1x-sp-2\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Rewrite the square as repeated multiplication. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf1y-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Each term interacts with every term. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf1z-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Distribute carefully. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf20-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > All products are now visible. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf21-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Both terms contain ab. </div><div id=\"implyzvcf22-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Combine like terms. </div></div></section>",
