    {
      "type": "eq",
      "start": 30,
      "end": 50,
      "html": "<section class=\"slide eq\"><ul class=\"eq-lines\"><li id=\"implyzvcg23\" class=\" eq-item eq-title \" > Testing with Variables </li><li id=\"implyzvcg24\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ (x+y)^2 $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcg25\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = (x+y)(x+y) $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcg26\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = x^2 + xy + xy + y^2 $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcg27\" class=\" eq-item eq-math \" > $$ = x^2 + 2xy + y^2 $$ </li><li id=\"implyzvcg28\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > This pattern appears throughout algebra. </li><li id=\"implyzvcg29\" class=\" eq-item eq-line \" > Careless expansion causes most mistakes. </li></ul><div class=\"eq-side-panel\"><div id=\"implyzvcg23-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > The identity works for all variables. </div><div id=\"implyzvcg24-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Replace a and b with x and y. </div><div id=\"implyzvcg25-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Again the bracket multiplies itself. </div><div id=\"implyzvcg26-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Write every multiplication step. </div><div id=\"implyzvcg27-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Combine the two xy terms. </div><div id=\"implyzvcg28-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Used in identities and factorization. </div><div id=\"implyzvcg29-sp-1\" class=\"eq-explain-item hidden\" > Always verify each multiplication. </div></div></section>",
